pageContext.claim: “Because the governor of the state of Washington is weak and the mayor is weak. And what they're doing is setting a precedent that's never been set before in this country. And these people that are taking over this incredible piece of real estate are obviously very good at real estate, maybe better than I was, because they paid nothing. They just took it over. And the police are somehow told not to be there.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is referring to a small area declared an "Autonomous Zone" in Seattle's Capitol Hill neighborhood -- which covers less than 1% of the entire city of Seattle, which is 142 square miles. The gathering was largely peaceful and was not attended by "domestic terrorists," as Trump has sometimes described the occupants. The Capitol Hill Autonomous Zone was established on June 8 and cleared of occupants by police on July 1.
